be possible in the world.

00:10:04.440 --> 00:10:07.010
It's interesting, so this
book actually started

00:10:07.010 --> 00:10:08.610
with some ideas from my students.

00:10:08.610 --> 00:10:11.030
In the early 1980s, toward the end

00:10:11.030 --> 00:10:13.570
of a U.S. foreign policy
course I taught when I was then

00:10:13.570 --> 00:10:16.170
on the faculty at the
University of California Davis,

00:10:16.170 --> 00:10:19.000
I had asked the students
