is not a safe path.

00:20:04.480 --> 00:20:06.940
It is indeed a dangerous activity.

00:20:06.940 --> 00:20:09.490
You appear dangerous to people
when you question their values,

00:20:09.490 --> 00:20:11.740
beliefs, or habits of a lifetime.

00:20:11.740 --> 00:20:14.060
You place yourself on the line
when you tell people what they need

00:20:14.060 --> 00:20:16.800
to hear rather than
what they want to hear."

00:20:16.800 --> 00:20:19.360
Gorbachev got killed
politically, some of the others

00:20:19.360 --> 00:20:21.340
in the book got assassinated.

00:20:21.340 --> 00:20:22.730
Charisma is an interesting quality,

00:20:22.730 --> 00:20:25.150
which is sort of what
people always point to,

00:20:25.150 --> 00:20:27.710
sort of the John Kennedy charisma.

00:20:27.710 --> 00:20:31.910
But -- and again, I'll talk some
about this now, and I'm happy to go

00:20:31.910 --> 00:20:33.400
into more detail when
we have discussion --

00:20:33.400 --> 00:20:35.060
in some ways it's backward.

00:20:35.060 --> 00:20:38.860 position:56%
I mean, Nelson Mandela is the iconic
case of a charismatic personality.

00:20:38.860 --> 00:20:40.700
But to jump ahead a little
bit, one of the people

00:20:40.700 --> 00:20:44.810
in the book is Yitzhak Rabin who
hardly fit the Kennedy image,

00:20:44.810 --> 00:20:48.540
this gruff old grandfatherly
guy who wasn't very good

00:20:48.540 --> 00:20:49.850
at being -- giving speeches.

00:20:49.850 --> 00:20:53.280
I was in Israel about three
weeks after his assassination,

00:20:53.280 --> 00:20:55.500
