00:35:44.040 --> 00:35:46.420
about the job description.

00:35:46.420 --> 00:35:49.940
And I'm going to do that with
a lot of pieces of this to sort

00:35:49.940 --> 00:35:52.310
of get pieces out along
the way to the book.

00:35:52.310 --> 00:35:54.460
But I think as we move
toward September

00:35:54.460 --> 00:35:58.320
when I think this decision gets
made, there's enormous lessons

00:35:58.320 --> 00:36:02.270
in the role that Hammarskjold
played.

00:36:02.270 --> 00:36:04.060
Mandela, of course,
is the iconic case

00:36:04.060 --> 00:36:08.000
of reconciliation among peoples,
leading the fight to end apartheid

00:36:08.000 --> 00:36:11.720
through peaceful means, and the
global icon that he embodied.

00:36:11.720 --> 00:36:14.410
The dignity with which he
endured his nearly three decades

00:36:14.410 --> 00:36:17.190
as a political prisoner inspired
so many people around the world,

00:36:17.190 --> 00:36:18.950
as well as in his own country.

00:36:18.950 --> 00:36:21.700
His commitment to reconciliation
fathered the rebirth

00:36:21.700 --> 00:36:25.940
of his own nation and presented the
world with a very different model

00:36:25.940 --> 00:36:28.660
from those seeking
retribution and revenge.

00:36:28.660 --> 00:36:32.390
His moral capacity to differentiate
between hatred of the system

00:36:32.390 --> 00:36:35.290
and hatred of whites was
a statesmanship contrast

00:36:35.290 --> 00:36:37.190
to the demagogic leaders
in so many other parts

00:36:37.190 --> 00:36:41.040
of the world fomenting
identity-based killings.

00:36:41.040 --> 00:36:44.050
For Sadat, who had built is
career quite conventionally

00:36:44.050 --> 00:36:47.220
through the Egyptian military and
was generally seen as a placeholder

00:36:47.220 --> 00:36:50.330
until a stronger successor
to Gamal Abdel Nasser rose,

00:36:50.330 --> 00:36:52.880
it was a long and surprising
journey.

00:36:52.880 --> 00:36:55.360
It ended with an assassin's
bullet, but before then along

00:36:55.360 --> 00:36:57.330
with U.S. President Jimmy Carter

00:36:57.330 --> 00:36:59.820
and Israeli Prime Minister
Menachem Begin --

00:36:59.820 --> 00:37:03.130
who again are prat of the story,
but not the crucial focus --

00:37:03.130 --> 00:37:06.270
he forged the first piece
of Arab/Israeli peace.

00:37:06.270 --> 00:37:09.660
And so, too, with Rabin who had
been the top military commander

00:37:09.660 --> 00:37:12.830
in the 1967 war that had
conquered the West Bank

00:37:12.830 --> 00:37:15.780
and other Arab territories.

00:37:15.780 --> 00:37:19.680
And as Defense Minister during the
1987 Palestinian Intifada allegedly

00:37:19.680 --> 00:37:22.580
[inaudible] of breaking bones,
became the Prime Minister

00:37:22.580 --> 00:37:26.430
who in 1993 shook hands with
PLO leader Yasser Arafat

00:37:26.430 --> 00:37:29.300
and signed a series of peace
agreements until he, too,

00:37:29.300 --> 00:37:31.590
was struck down by an assassin.

00:37:31.590 --> 00:37:33.880
True, the pieces of peace
they laid were partial,

00:37:33.880 --> 00:37:36.950
but without them there would be
even less chance of ever getting

00:37:36.950 --> 00:37:40.950
to a full Israeli peace --
full Arab/Israeli peace.

00:37:40.950 --> 00:37:43.950
And in the spirit of the
impact held, not just the --

00:37:43.950 --> 00:37:47.750
impact had, not just position
held, I'm trying to bring in others

00:37:47.750 --> 00:37:51.900 position:56%
to demonstrate how in this
particular case of Northern Ireland,

00:37:51.900 --> 00:37:53.540
Betty Williams and Mairead Corrigan

00:37:53.540 --> 00:37:58.440 position:56%
who in 1976 founded the Northern
Ireland Women of Peace at the height

00:37:58.440 --> 00:38:01.540
of the violence of the
troubles as everyday people

00:38:01.540 --> 00:38:05.320
who in their own ways demonstrated
transformational statesmanship.

00:38:05.320 --> 00:38:06.740
The troubles had taken
the death toll

00:38:06.740 --> 00:38:13.350
from about 16 in 1969
to 500 by 1972.

00:38:13.350 --> 00:38:16.850
And while there was never only
one factor, these two women

00:38:16.850 --> 00:38:19.720
